<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880225-0124 </DOCNO><HL> General Host Completes Sale </HL><SO> </SO><CO> GH </CO><IN> TNM </IN><DATELINE> STAMFORD, Conn.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   General Host Corp. said it completed the sale of its American Salt Co. unit to a group led by the unit's management for $22 million and a $9 million subordinated note.    American Salt, based in Mission, Kan., produces salt products used in water softening, food processing and road de-icing. The acquiring company is headed by Ronald J. Nugent, American Salt president.    General Host operates Frank's Nursery andamp; Crafts Inc. and Flower Time Inc., which sell lawn and garden products, crafts and Christmas merchandise. </TEXT></DOC>